<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14438">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Composite%20Materials.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14439">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14439 mb-requirement-id-14440">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while working with composite materials and what you should do to
        anticipate, mitigate, and prevent, and respond to these hazards.
        Describe the appropriate safety gear and clothing that should be used
        when working with composite materials. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tXmTLRSMZSM" target="_blank"
          >Fibreglass Safety 101 (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/oVBSWJCSK4E" target="_blank"
          >How to Stay Clean and Safe Working With Fiberglass (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14439 mb-requirement-id-14441">
        (b) Explain the precautions that must be taken when handling, storing,
        and disposing of resins, reinforcements, and other materials used in
        composites. Include in your discussion the importance of health, safety,
        and environmental responsibility and awareness. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tVwFisroxrg" target="_blank"
          >How to Dispose of Epoxy Resin Leftovers and Used Materials (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://allanchem.com/ultimate-guide-to-resin-handling-safety/"
          target="_blank"
          >Ultimate Guide to Resin Handling Safety (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14439 mb-requirement-id-14442">
        (c) Describe what a safety data sheet (SDS) is and tell why it is used.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_yWF-w3CwmU" target="_blank"
          >Safety Data Sheets Training (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14443">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14443 mb-requirement-id-14444">
        (a) Explain what composite materials are. Include a brief history of
        composites and how they have developed. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/WYqCnEvTRUQ?si=4MqVQJIT2aQ-1nsr"
          target="_blank"
          >Intro to Composites (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/8tEf_X9Rzts?si=El0NGrvMMuSvJ3w7"
          target="_blank"
          >What is a Composite? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14443 mb-requirement-id-14445">
        (b) Compare the similarities and differences between composites and
        wood, aluminum, copper, and steel. Describe the physical, electrical,
        mechanical, corrosive, flammability, cost, and other such properties.
        For each of these raw materials, give one example of how it can be
        shaped and used for a specific application. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XbX4xY1sqQo" target="_blank"
          >Properties of Materials (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14446">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Describe how composite materials are made. Then do the following: <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/gYTjC8GIwcU" target="_blank"
        >How Do Composites Work? (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14446 mb-requirement-id-14447">
        (a) Discuss three different composite reinforcement materials, their
        positive and negative characteristics, and their uses. Obtain the SDS
        for each one and discuss the toxicity, disposal, and safe-handling
        sections for these materials. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jsAJIMKEoZQ" target="_blank"
          >Introduction to Fibres (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14446 mb-requirement-id-14448">
        (b) Discuss three different resins used in composites, their positive
        and negative characteristics, and their uses. Obtain the SDS for each
        one and discuss the toxicity, disposal, and safe-handling sections for
        these materials. Include thermoset resins and thermoplastic resins in
        your discussion. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/yQo4ucV3jfA" target="_blank"
          >Introduction to Matrix Materials (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14446 mb-requirement-id-14449">
        (c) For each of the three resins you chose for requirement 3(b), think
        of a new application that might be worth developing.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14450">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      With your parent or guardian's permission and your counselor's approval do
      ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14450 mb-requirement-id-14451">
        (a) Visit a company that manufactures or repairs products made with
        composites. Discuss what you learn with your counselor.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14450 mb-requirement-id-14452">
        (b) Find three composites-related websites. Share and discuss what you
        learn with your counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14453">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do the following: <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Ry7_Yuo-FYM?si=VwPF2eUQYD3FSvbz" target="_blank"
        >STEM Flix™ - Fun with Composite Materials with Science Bob (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/vxKlbik4QjM?si=5lLZ-vLZFHDSm_As" target="_blank"
        >How to Dispose of Epoxy Resin Leftovers and Used Materials (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/scvXKij1hQ0" target="_blank"
        >How to Hand Lay Up a Carbon Fibre Skateboard (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14453 mb-requirement-id-14454">
        (a) Use composite materials to complete two projects, at least one of
        which must come from the <em>Composite Materials</em> merit badge
        pamphlet. The second project may come from the pamphlet OR may be one
        you select on your own that has been approved by your counselor in
        advance.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14453 mb-requirement-id-14455">
        (b) With your counselor's assistance, find an appropriate site where the
        projects can be safely completed under your counselor's supervision
        and/or the supervision of an adult approved by your counselor who is
        knowledgeable about composites.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14453 mb-requirement-id-14456">
        (c) With your counselor, determine how the finished projects will be
        evaluated. Using those guidelines, evaluate the completed projects with
        your counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14457">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14457 mb-requirement-id-14458">
        (a) Explore careers related to the Composite Materials merit badge.
        Research one career to learn about the training and education needed,
        costs, job prospects, salary, job duties, and career advancement. Your
        research methods may include—with your parent or guardian's
        permission—an internet or library search, an interview with a
        professional in the field, or a visit to a location where people in this
        career work. Discuss with your counselor both your findings and what
        about this profession might make it an interesting career. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DtosXFgP7C4" target="_blank"
          >Materials Engineer - Careers in Science and Engineering (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/c0EXAuWkMqA" target="_blank"
          >Materials Science - a Building Block for the Future of Aerospace
          Technologies (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/j_xotv7npsQ" target="_blank"
          >My Job in F1: Rachel, Materials Science Engineer (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14457 mb-requirement-id-14459">
        (b) Explore how you could use knowledge and skills from the
        <i>Composite Materials</i> merit badge to pursue a hobby or interest.
        Research any training needed, expenses, and organizations that promote
        or support it. Discuss with your counselor what short-term and long-term
        goals you might have if you pursued this. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rYYuDt8Z2cY" target="_blank"
          >Surfboard Shaping and Glassing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/s2aS1G6yp-4" target="_blank"
          >Making a Skateboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
